RE: Venting (30-01-2013 08:54 PM)Richard Stuckmeyer Wrote: (30-01-2013 08:33 PM)Anjele Wrote: Try being a little more decent and people may be civil to you. We are a community here and some of us feel more like family and we don't like to have the people we interact with here routinely be attacked, as you have done...frequently.
There has been some lashing out against you and yours from people you have treated like crap...is that really so surprising.
I would imagine you wife is a very nice person and if there is a sainthood waiting for anyone, it would be her.
You fueled a fire and threw her in. Perhaps you have some issues, can't believe this is what the doctor prescribed. Didn't know that an effective Rx was acting like one of the biggest jerks that's been around her for while. Find another hobby, make some duck calls, or whittle something...maybe you could torture small animals.
I agree, I came in here with guns ablazing. I came here directly from a Christian forum where atheists were constantly coming in and acting exactly as I did when I came in. I was determined to kick ass and take names, giving tit for tat. I admit, I have met just a few, civil atheists on here. Most of you have been just as big of asses as I am. I can handle that. Like I keep saying, I dish it out and I can take it, better than most of you can. I keep telling you all over and over and over that everything I say is my opinion and then you all keep getting mad and telling me that everything you say is fact. Do you just expect me to roll over and accept that? Of course I get sarcastic, you all get sarcastic too. I told you, God told me (yeah, that's right) my purpose here is not to teach you but to give you opportunities to add fuel to your own funeral pyres. You people blaspheme the awesome Creator of the universe (my opinion) and wonder why I get upset? How come you only do this to Christians? Not to Muslims, Hindus, Buddhists or whatever, only Christians. I dare you to go to a Muslim forum and flame the way you do the Christian forums. I go to Muslim forums and have very nice converstions. They are actually civil as long as I dont try to tell them that their beliefs are a bunch of crap. I've made good friends out of Muslims.
No, that's a lie. I did not throw my wife in. She, against my advice, wanted to enter hell. So, I let her. Now she understands what I have been saying about atheists.
Yep, this is exactly what the doctor ordered. My mind feels clearer each day. Yep, I'm a jerk. Is there another point to this?
Sorry, no good at that stuff and I love little animals.
If you're willing to ignore those who wish you rile you up and have a civil discussion then a civil discussion is what you will have. If you pack your arguments and discussion with trollish fervor then you'll get exactly that in return. People here can be very nice if you're willing to be the same. But take one bite of a troll bar and you'll be shitting bricks every day you log on. After reading what you've posted in this thread I got:
"I got mad that some immature atheists came on our forums to be assholes. So because I'm incapable of acting like an adult, I'm going to go troll some other forums and show them that I can be an asshole too!"
You'll find usually the people that take the time out of their day to register on forums simply to troll have little to nothing better to do. If you have things you enjoy spending your time doing, I would recommend spending time doing that instead. Being an asshole rarely changes minds.
More realistically the average person lives around 27,000 to 30,000 days. Every day you spend your existence "trolling others" or "trying to be a badass on the internet" is one less day you have to soak in the world around you, enjoy life and the things that actually matter.
I'm sure you went on your forums to enjoy like minded people. We enjoy this forum because we enjoy like minded people. If your existence and entire purpose here is to spend time annoying others, you could be spending the same amount of time elsewhere with people you truly enjoy. Nuisance has little impact on decisions in life for others, aside from causing nuisance. I'm not trying to be an asshole... just trying to provide some outside perspective to how I've seen your posts here thus far.
