Never said mine is ok and yours isn't. If I'm being sarcastic or silly, it's an attempt to toss a bit of humor into a thread that perhaps I see as "too serious" - sometimes humor is a great ailment so both parties can at least find some common ground. What good is life if you can't laugh now and then?
I'm sorry you've had that experience on your forums. It's safe to say that the vast majority of us here won't and don't bother to do such a thing. But there is always an exception to the rule. It is the internet after all... statistically trolls are everywhere. Go to a Harley forum and you're bound to see some squiddlies hop on there telling them how their bikes suck. Go to a sportbike forum and surely someone will tell them that their crotch rockets are just tools of death and for kids who can't ride. The same goes for any crowd where there are people who are passionate about their views on a subject.
Regardless, sorry you had that experience. I've certainly got no hate for you, and my attempts at humor in the threads you posted in were just that, attempts at humor. No intent to ridicule you, nor your beliefs, just make a little light of things. Nothing more nothing less.
I did indeed miss the part where it said you are housebound. Sorry to hear that. I can see where forum time may be more timely spent. I enjoy forums as well since I enjoy discussions with people. I don't get halfway decent discussion in my parts most of the time, and there are certainly plenty of great discussions online, regardless of the subject.
Anyway, I hope you enjoy your stay on the forums should you choose to stay and participate. We're not all assholes (most of the time) 30-01-2013, 11:27 PM #16
