RE: Venting I don't see where there was much said against your wife. A lot about you and to be sure, a lot of condescension toward her but again, not much in the way of an attack.
That said, I don't care for personal attacks of any kind but they seem to be a permanent thread in the fabric of internet forums so if you're on one, expect them. I choose not to give them much attention and I certainly try not to stoop to that level of discourse. I also don't seem to find myself in online flame wars. It's kind of like being in bar fights.... if you aren't cheating at pool, you'll likely not be in one. And if you aren't even in the bar, you'll never be in one. ;-)
Getting back on the topic of wives/family... there's nothing someone can say about my wife on the internet that's going to affect me. The reason is because I know that when someone launches an attack on an internet forum, he's saying more about himself than he is the person he's attacking.
It's quite sad actually. That people feel the need to attack others in order to feel better about themselves.
